    {
      "id": "mode-label",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 65,
      "y": 460,
      "width": 170,
      "height": 160,
      "text": "Mode Comparison\n\nEnforce (default):\n• Streaming: OFF\n• L2: sync redact\n• L2b: active\n\nAudit:\n• Streaming: ON\n• L2: async log only\n• L2b: not registered",
      "fontSize": 12,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "strokeColor": "#495057",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "groupIds": [],
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 11002,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 11002,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Mode Comparison\n\nEnforce (default):\n• Streaming: OFF\n• L2: sync redact\n• L2b: active\n\nAudit:\n• Streaming: ON\n• L2: async log only\n• L2b: not registered",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "baseline": 153
    },
    {
      "id": "flow-step-1",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 50,
      "y": 700,
      "width": 1180,
      "height": 130,
      "text": "Flow: ① User sends message → L3 audits inbound (async, cannot block) → ② L1 injects DLP policy into LLM context → ③ LLM processes with DLP policy active\n→ ④ If LLM calls tool: L2 scans tool output via Purview sync (spawnSync+curl). If BLOCKED → redacts content before LLM sees it\n→ ⑤ LLM generates response (sees redacted output + has DLP policy) → ⑥ L2b scans outbound message via Purview async. If BLOCKED → replaces with DLP notice\n→ ⑦ Message delivered via Telegram sendMessage\n\nDefense-in-depth: L0 (Azure OpenAI content filter) + L1 (prompt guard) + L2 (sync tool redaction) + L2b (async response blocking) + L3 (audit logging)",
      "fontSize": 14,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "strokeColor": "#495057",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "angle": 0,
      "groupIds": [],
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 12001,
      "version": 2,
      "versionNonce": 12001,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Flow: ① User sends message → L3 audits inbound (async, cannot block) → ② L1 injects DLP policy into LLM context → ③ LLM processes with DLP policy active\n→ ④ If LLM calls tool: L2 scans tool output via Purview sync (spawnSync+curl). If BLOCKED → redacts content before LLM sees it\n→ ⑤ LLM generates response (sees redacted output + has DLP policy) → ⑥ L2b scans outbound message via Purview async. If BLOCKED → replaces with DLP notice\n→ ⑦ Message delivered via Telegram sendMessage\n\nDefense-in-depth: L0 (Azure OpenAI content filter) + L1 (prompt guard) + L2 (sync tool redaction) + L2b (async response blocking) + L3 (audit logging)",
      "lineHeight": 1.25,
      "baseline": 120
    }
  ],
